original_dir = pathlib.Path('data/kaggle_dogs_vs_cats/train')
new_base_dir = pathlib.Path('data/kaggle_dogs_vs_cats_small')

def make_subset(subset_name, start_index, end_index):
    for category in ("cat", "dog"):
        dir = new_base_dir / subset_name / category
        os.makedirs(dir)
        fnames = [f"{category}.{i}.jpg" for i in range(start_index, end_index)]
        for fname in fnames:
            shutil.copyfile(src=original_dir / fname,
                            dst=dir / fname)

data_folder = pathlib.Path('data/kaggle_dogs_vs_cats_small')

train_dataset = image_dataset_from_directory(
    data_folder / 'train',
    labels='inferred',
    label_mode='int',
    image_size=(180, 180),
    batch_size=32)
validation_dataset = image_dataset_from_directory(
    data_folder / 'validation',
    labels='inferred',
    label_mode='int',
    image_size=(180, 180),
    batch_size=32)
test_dataset = image_dataset_from_directory(
    data_folder / 'test',
    labels='inferred',
    label_mode='int',
    image_size=(180, 180),
    batch_size=32)

for data_batch, labels_batch in train_dataset:
    print("data batch shape:", data_batch.shape)
    print("labels batch shape:", labels_batch.shape)
    break

In [ ]:
tf.random.set_seed(42)
self_define_model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Rescaling(1./255, input_shape=(180, 180, 3)),
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(16, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),
    tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])
self_define_model.compile(optimizer='rmsprop', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    
self_define_model.summary()

vgg16_redefine = tf.keras.Sequential()
vgg16_redefine.add(tf.keras.layers.Rescaling(1./255, input_shape=(180, 180, 3)))
for layer in vgg16.layers[1:]:
    vgg16_redefine.add(layer)
vgg16_redefine.add(tf.keras.layers.Flatten())
vgg16_redefine.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(256))
vgg16_redefine.add(tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5))
vgg16_redefine.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation="sigmoid"))

from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, classification_report, precision_recall_curve

validation_batch = list(validation_dataset)[0]
validation_data, validation_label = validation_batch[0], validation_batch[1]

preds_vgg = best_vgg16.predict(validation_data).reshape(32)
preds_self = self_define_model.predict(validation_data).reshape(32)

precision_vgg = tf.keras.metrics.Precision()(validation_label, preds_vgg).numpy()
precision_self = tf.keras.metrics.Precision()(validation_label, preds_self).numpy()
print('\tVGG model Precision:{:.2f}%'.format(precision_vgg*100))
print('\tself define model Precision:{:.2f}%'.format(precision_vgg*100))

recall_vgg = tf.keras.metrics.Recall()(validation_label, preds_vgg).numpy()
recall_self = tf.keras.metrics.Recall()(validation_label, preds_self).numpy()
print('\n\tVGG model Recall:{:.2f}%'.format(recall_vgg*100))
print('\tself define model Recall:{:.2f}%'.format(recall_self*100))

f1_vgg = 2 * (precision_vgg * recall_vgg) / (precision_vgg + recall_vgg)
f1_self = 2 * (precision_self * recall_self) / (precision_self + recall_self)
print('\n\tVGG Model F1 Score:{:.2f}%'.format(f1_vgg*100))
print('\tSelf Define Model F1 Score:{:.2f}%'.format(f1_self*100))

6. Conclusions¶

  • From the results the self-define model is superior to vgg16
  • In fact when I first used vgg16, the accuracy was significantly higher than the self-define model.
  • However, there was a bug in the later work, and after fixing the bug the accurace was never as good as the self-define model. I haven't found the reason yet.
